         <div type="apparatus">
            <p>i, l.1 <foreign xml:lang="grc">Θεόφιλ<ex>ος</ex>
               </foreign>
Reinach; earlier editors could interpret nothing.</p>
            <p>l. 3. <seg cert="low">
                  <foreign xml:lang="grc">μασ<supplied reason="lost">α</supplied>ύρη </foreign>
               </seg>
Kirchhoff; <seg cert="low">
                  <foreign xml:lang="grc">Μασ<supplied reason="lost">σ</supplied>άρη</foreign>
               </seg> Ramsay; <seg cert="low">
                  <foreign xml:lang="grc">Μαζλαρη</foreign>
               </seg> Reinach;
it was Grégoire who recognized the abbreviation mark standing
for <foreign xml:lang="grc">κε</foreign> and resolved the text, reading
<foreign xml:lang="grc">Θεοφίλῳ</foreign> accordingly in l.1.</p>
            <p>ii, l. 1,  <foreign xml:lang="grc">κ<choice>
                     <sic>ο</sic>
                     <corr>ω</corr>
                  </choice>νστα<supplied reason="lost">ν</supplied>τ<supplied reason="lost" cert="low">ῖνος</supplied>
               </foreign> Reinach; <foreign xml:lang="grc">κονστα<supplied reason="lost">ντῖνος</supplied>
               </foreign>
Grégoire.</p>
         </div>
         <div type="translation">
            <ab>i. Lord, help your servant Theophilos, butcher.</ab>
            <ab>ii. Konstantinos, deacon.</ab>
         </div>
